items.text: Try the Lao Ban Beancurd - #beancurd #chinese
Tried Whitley prawns noodles. Alright but still not a good as Wah Kee big prawn noodles at Pek Kio
Try J&J; hawker. All the food is well-cooked. Recommended: Wagyu Beef Rice.
#01-99 - 蚝煎v gd, 蚝v fresh
Try this Penang Prawn Noodle #01-143. Cheap and  delicious!!! Soft pork rib meat and fresh prawn.
Whitley Rd Big Prawn Noodle must eat!! 
It's a great place for friend gathering. Whereby each of you can order a dish.  At the end, the table would be full of variety yummy dish.

For those who like deserts, try the 三姑糖水at #01-155. Their Ah...Boling is very nice. Well done for their "Yam cream with glutinous rice" too. Those who like deserts and do not like it too sweet. Here !
Personally I feel Blanco Court Rico Kway Chap is ok is normal.  The meat is well cook and tender. However the rest of the stuff is salty. The chilli spoilt e whole thing as it taste sour.
Try the deep fried durian, smell good, taste good and it's just good!! 
Try soft n smooth Chee Cheong Fun @ #01-155! yummy!
Durian ice blended is awesome possum.
Warung Pak Wahab @ #01-034
Dong Ji fried kway teow better than the lao fu zi stall's!! Try it
Where can I find the mutton soup here !?help
J & J beef noodles
Back for the butter crab again. Nomnomnom.
01-91 century egg lean meat porridge = $3
#01-121 stall selling Fish Head Bee Hoon. Long constant Q.... Hmmm is it supposed to be bland?

I wonder if the curry puff here taste good? I want to try but its closed today:( however, even the outdoor seat is little not clean, but it's good to have breakfast here! The weather is good today! :)
Char kway teow and lor mee worth the super long Q.
Head to #01-155 "freshly made Chee cheong fun" 2nd row beside "Ali shan curry fish head". The stall name says it all :)
lao pan tao huay! waited for 1hour! worth it!!! the softest beancurd ever.
Must try the Taiwan Porridge...
Try the Loh Bak - Pork Roll - #lohbak #hokkien #pork
Lao Fu Zi Char Kway Tiao!
Steamboat steam fish very yummy.
Pasta Manna...shiok! 'Nuff said.
Cockles nice what...................
Lao Ban Soya Beancurd - Unique taste! Extremely smooth n light texture! Must try!
Awesome prawn mee soup Albert Street and lor mee
Waiting for my Satay!! Chuan Kee Satay @ #01-85
SOON HENG SUGARCANE.... remember 7-8 years ago, a giant cup launched and was titled by 8Days magazine BEST SUGARCANE(100% PURE)...
Lao ban beancurd is smooth as custard. 01-127
Stall 105 has delicious roasted chicken rice.
Try the claypot soya sauce chicken that might just be the last of its kind despite how delicious it is! Also the one person steamboat and the western chicken/pork chop are good too!
This hor fun is good.
http://mobile.aaiia.biz/ and www.aaiia.biz. Send this to 10 of your friends and get free Petrol Voucher now. Blk 351 Jurong East St. 31 01-79 S(600351) Eric Choy
Hougang Jing Jia Mutton Soup (#01-123) is not the Chinese herb kind (New World) but really mutton soup. Might get a little too mutton-y. Mutton is tender though and tasty. Chilli is normal. So-so.
Try the geylang lor 20 banana fried fritters. Goreng pisang yums!!
Warung Pak Wahab @unit number #01-034 selling delicious halal malay cuisine.
#01-94 Homemade Springroll standard dropped pretty badly.
Lucky Char Kuey Tiao worth Q-ing. Also try e Fresh juice ice blend next to it.
Durian craving? Try 717 trading's durian crepes.. Its yummy!! Only $3.80. But watch out if you are heaty! Hee~ ;)
Mattar Road Seafood Barbecue. Blk 51, Old Airport Road Food Centre, #01-63, Singapore 390051. 8 DAYS eat - Crabs. Chilli Crab (signature) Female Crab and White Pepper Male Crab
Yummy roasted chicken rice! #01-119 Weng Hua Yuen Hainanese Chicken
Try the dessert stall #01-59 晶晶冷热甜品.. The stall with thr most hello kitty arrangment ! Best bobo cha cha mus eat hot !
Albert street prawn noodle is soooo terrible! Pls don try it unless u like ur soup bland and tasteless!

Extremely dissatisfied with Nam Sing Hokkien Mee,30 mins ago they said I was next, it's been 1 hour already but still have not arrived. And they forgot to add prawns for me even though I paid $2 more!
Try #01-112 for the caramelised char siew. Soft and tasty. Highly recommended
The best foods in Singapore can be found here. Kway chap and hokkien mee here are excellent! Be prepared for long queues/waits though.
Thiam Seng Seafood  #01-152  Wed - Mon : 4.00pm - 11.00pm
Aglio Olio E Peperoncino from Pasta Manna! Pasta with premium quality at a low price. Simply can't go wrong!
sad to say..Lao Fu Zi char kway tiao..standard dropped..
Try the wantan noodle here or crocodile meat stall. One of the best. The noodle stall need to take Q no. somemore
Toa payoh rojak is good,but the tau pok they give too little for $4...Hougang jing jia mutton soup not bad too..the ribs very fatty..Also try lao pan(beancurd),like creme brulee..almond version rox
The tao payoh rojar is a must after your meal here. The thick paste provide with jelly fish is comparable to the one situated in Tao Payoh HDB hub. Order the $3 serving if possible. :)
Must try #01-17 house of dessert. The ah Balling and black sesame soup is damn nice.
Bean Flower Water #01-102 has nice Grass Jelly drinks and Soya Bean Curd! Try the Grass Jelly with Aloe Vera, REFRESHING!
Lor mee is very nice, wanton noodle, pig intestine are very nice too
Ng tong San herb tea
Try the Wanton Mee
Fairly standard hawker center with a big selection of more Chinese and Singapore type flavors. I wish there were a few Indian options, but what is here is pretty good.  Good seafood.
Lao fu zi kuey tiao used to be nice,after it became popular it simply sucks and all u get is kuey tiao with few cockles and tiny bits of fishcake
Prawn noodles to die for!!!
The taufu fa is very nice
Many wonderful food at this food centre. Try to avoid peak hours as seats are hard to find. There must be a stall for you.
The fish soup from stall #01-121 (branch of the famed fish soup stall @ Maxwell Centre) is the best. Honestly there's no need to bother about it's competitors.
To-Ricos kway chap is da bomb. Super long queue during lunch hour however.
Prawn mee!!
Tiong Bahru Lor Mee very long Q
Fried pig intestine is a MUST try! =)
lao ban soyabean is a must try....super long queues
Must try: chilli crab! It will never disappoint your taste buds.
Ru ji kitchen,meepok best
Prepare for the Q. Esp. at char kuey teow, loh mee and the mee pok stalls. Note to myself: no vinegar for my mee pok nx time!
cho kee wanton mee has a very old-school taste; must try.
Char kway teow. I prefer the sweeter, complete taste @Lao Fu Zi #01-12. The lap cheong (Chinese sausage) @Dong Ji #01-138 had a musty smell & its less tasty dish was not worth queuing for
Must try ....
Came here for Saturday breakfast - not too crowded, and the most important stalls are open. Don't miss the Xin Mei Xiang lor mee or the 51 Soya tau huay.
$1.20, Award Winning Soya Beancurd by QQ Soya Bean at Old Airport Road. Featured in Makansutra, The Newpaper, 8 Days, Soshiok.com & inSing.com. Minimum purchase of 4 coupons.
Go somewhere else!!! It's not cheap here!!!
Try out the soups from "SOUP & PASTA 168" located at #01-168 awesome mushroom soup. And the white bread with it!
All the local delicacies!! Go before 630 to find good seats (with fan nearby) for dinner
Lots of nice food found here!
Tiong Bahru Lor Mee very yummy.  A lot of fish meat.
Mattar Road Seafood BBQ has good crabs
Awesome chee cheong fan
Soya beancurd by Lao Pan is famous. The texture is really unique, you have to try it for yourself!
One of the few if not the best Hawker centers still in existence in Singapore. Lao Fu Zi char kuay teow quite close to the Malaysian style. Hope some traditions here get preserved
Try the Satay Bee Hoon - #beehoon #singaporean #noodle #satay
二十四味凉茶 (24-herbs tea) at S$3 per bottle from Ng Tong San Herb Tea stall #01-50. The non-sweetened version has got mild refreshing fragrant of herbs, eventhough some still feel its bitter :-P
Get the rojak from TOA PAYOH ROJAK stall! Remember to add all the ingredients together e.g. Cuttlefish, century egg and taopok! Worth it!
Mr cook herbal chicken n blanco court kway chap
Very competitive where we have a few "Tao Huey" stalls vying for attention but Lor Mee is one of the authentic tasted here, I guess
One of my favourite Ngor Hiang food stall: Seng Kee Ngo Hiang Prawn Cracker stall at Old Airport Road Food Centre, #01-29. Opens from evening till night about 11+pm. Good for finger food / pot luck.
Just go in the morning and follow the queues. Plenty to choose from.
Best Bean curd
A lot of nice food... Surprisingly this new store is not bad!
Blanco Court Kuay Chap is nothing fantastic, don't waste your time queuing.
The 132 mini steamboat is nice. Must try the herbal soup base. Best !!!
Nam Sing Hokkien Mee has the longest most infuriating wait. Make sure u know ur table number, self service for tables 175 onwards. Annoyed even before I can eat. >:(
Hua Kee Hougang Famous Wan Ton Mee, the best!!!
Avoid coming here on Weekend / P.h as most of the stalls will be long queue or long waiting time~
I've been here 52 times and have tried 99 dishes. We loved: 1) Sugarcane Juice @ Mei Xing Coffee #01-03 2) Soya Beancurd (Almond) @ Lao Ban Soya Beancurd #01-127. See Top 10 dishes on Foodmento:
Try the Yummy Thai #01-161. The Seafood fried rice is delicious.
Minced pork noodle #01-124. Is a must to try if u r at old airport hawker centre.
mee sua near the entrance is the best ~
No harm trying the 'lucky fried kway tiao' opposite 'lao fu zi kway tiao'... I find it better :)
Lao Ban beancurd is a definite must try, Lao Fu Zi char kway teow is one of my loves. Albert street prawn noodle ain't too yummy for my liking.
The lor mee here is worth queuing! Mad delicious.. I never get tired of eating lor mee.
Minced Mix Noodles  #01-128  Tue - Fri : 11.00am - 8.30pm  Sat - Sun : 9.30am - 8.30pm
Try the Wanton Mee
Sheng De Kung Fu Hokkien mee stall uncle is fcuked up. questions u when u ask for extra plate, saying no supply of plates unless u ordered $5 or more. cmon, hw much can a styrofoam plate cost!?
Had some decent satay bee hoon. Poor selection of malay food, plenty of Chinese stalls selling the same things. Pushy drink sellers
Food;) and Lao ban
Try the soya beancurd
Must eat 老伴 beancurd! Worth the queue.
If u come here often, try J & J special beef noodle, #01-162. No wait during busy hrs and very good stuff.
Kidney Mee Sua (#01-69) must try... Black dark soup... From Bedok 511!!!
DIY popiah: Fortune Food #01-94 sells handmade (actually central kitchen) popiah skin ($15/kg), ground peanuts, crispy bits, chilli sauce, etc to host ur own popiah party @ home. They deliver too!

The stall named Western Barbeque here is to die for. Their garlic sauce is amazing. Located at the back row, they are the other branch of the one at the hawker ctr at Bedok Int. Hv been loyal for yrs.
The best Thai food in town. Yummy Thai at 01-161.
Lau Fu Zi charkwaytiao, prawn noodles and wanton mee
Dong ji char kway teow! #01-138 (: uncle is friendly and cooks per order, doesn't mass cook, so I presume the quality should be better. Smells awesome.
51 tau huay is JIMPPPP
Mini hotpot value for $
Stalls 01-07, 01-12, 01-32, 01-116 and 01-135 are the most famous! Get in early as they close when they sell out!
Nice and affordable local food
For a guilty pleasure try the fried oyster omelette next to the whitley big prawn noodle store. So yummy!!!
Take your pic. Everything is good here. Albert street prawn mee is pretty famous!
The char siew from Roast Paradise is yummy!
Wanton Mee!
上海小笼包 must try !
Try the beancurd at store '51 Soya Bean'. Very soft n smooth. They hav durian beancurd too.
Fried durian sold here!
51 is much better than Laoban or Rochor
Try the J&J; beef noodle #01-162. good beef soup and other beef noodles
Cao Ji Wanton mee is worth a try! Sedap la!
Lao ban beancurd. Best!
Pasta manna 's carbonara is my fav ....restaurant quality but hawker price ...only $6...fast in serving aso
The most valuable hawker centre ever in Singapore
Pasta manna #01-84... Serve good pasta.. Look nice n main point is cheap..
This is one of my favorite hawker centres in Singapore. Many delicious food can be found here, you'll be spoilt for choice!
Try their dimsums. Really good
wang wang crispy puff http://www.hungrygowhere.com/singapore/wang_wang_crispy_curry_puff/
Oyster Omelet
I love the curry pork rice, yum yum
what's not to like! Everything is great.
Steam fresh fish from Steamboat#01-148.

The biggest piece. Not a honest stall!! Pls refer to both the plates above the pic. Both cost $26 in total! After telling them we were told tt the sotong was $10 as told by another auntie, they charge
Crocodile meat is super worthy and yummy! Gd for health.
Hua Kee has most probably one of the best Wanton Mees in SG
Long queue at xin MRI xiang lor mee... As always!!
My favorite fish ball noodle!
Holy Grill's Grilled Fish with Cajun Spice just taste simply marvelous! Soft and tender meat, with great-tasting sauce. You will definitely want to come back again for more.
Wah! Chee cheong fun so pathetic! The one beside alisan curry fish head! $2 somemore. -.- fail!
Italian pasta stall...a definite must try!
Whitley Road Big Prawn Noodles are awesome!
Love their aglio olio! Must try!!
Jimmy's Coffee is the best here. Corner stall located closest to car park entry facing old airport road, opposite AliShan mixed rice stall
Lao fu Zi char kway teow is the best!!
Soo kee fishball noodles are the bomb!
Jing Jing Dessert store @ 01-59 is cheap & good! $1.20 for a bowl of ice kachang!
Stall 1153 selling really expensive sugar cane drink.. 2.70 a big cup..
Fragrant Charcoal Crispy Egg Tart by Chef Hong H.K. Bakery at Old Airport Road Market & Food Centre.
Shitty food. I wonder what's all the hype about.
Yummy !
Definitely 老伴beancurd!
#01-148 Steamboat, best for the fresh steam  fish.
Wanton noodle, Prawn noodle, Western Food & Nasi Lemak... the best in e East...
Rojak is best !!
Banana fritters! Must try!! :-D
Zichar. Hong Yun #01-61 fires up mediocre zichar rice dishes. Non-existent vege, 2 prawns, $4
Kway chup here is the most popular in SG: 30min queueing time though!
#01-166 Hougang Otah: Do not patronize as the uncle is rude. I merely asked if the otah is warm (as we were going to eat it there), he gave me a scolding saying even people who buy 100 don't ask.
All the oldies but goodies local food. May this place never be redeveloped!
Lao ban tauhuay is good but forever long queue! 51 tauhuay is equally good though!
Western food is a must try! Awesome dishes w different sauces. V filling too!!
Lao ban bean curd, black carrot cake facing the road.
Must Try Lao Ban BEANCURD!!!
veg bee hoon nice bigass tau kee
Kallang Western BBQ. Chicken Chop and cutlet sedap. ask for the garlic sauce, owners own concoction. Fu Dao satay, 40 cents a stick inclusive of its black pepper satay.
Stall 61 yummssss
It is good
#01-44 Momo's Mini Pau superb !!!
Chuan Kee satay, apparently
My fave stall is Ah Hock Fried Hokkien Mee. Waiting time is bet 20 to 45 mins everyday! Close on Mon. Another must eat is the Fried Oysters from $4.....
The Char Kuey Tiao @ #01-30 is a must try!
Their kidney Meesua is good too! Must try! Generous servings of meat.
Prawn mee, Satay and Rojak is the bombz!
#01-107Crocodile Kingdom鳄鱼大王 must try honry crocodile ribs 蜜汁鳄鱼排骨$12 n herbal crocodile soup养生汤$8/12 remember to ask add skin addition $8 n other 煮炒style of crocodile meat.
Lao Ban soyabeancurd is a MUST TRY!
The always long queueing Kway Chap is a must try here! Especially on Sunday morning...
Jelly dessert lovers! I love Lao Pan's handmade & freshly made soybean curd jellies. #01-127
51 beat Lao Ban hands down, at least to me.
老伴豆花 nice! So smooth & it just melt in yr mouth. Worth to queqe or ta bao. Lao fu zhi char kway teow not really nice as told for my taste. The one opp lao fu zhi is nicer to my taste:)
so many goodfood...
Dong Ji char kway tiao! :)
